  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "Current law allows the state to locate an automated vehicle identification system (AVIS) on a highway that is part of the federal interstate highway system but prohibits a county, city and county, or municipality (local government) from doing so. The bill authorizes a local government to locate an AVIS on a highway that is part of the federal interstate highway system.(Note: This summary applies to this bill as introduced.)"
    }
  ],
